## Calculate Your Own Error Cost

Here is the framework. Five minutes with a calculator and your own numbers.

**Step 1: Establish your baseline.**

- Daily order volume: ___
- Estimated error rate (use 3% if you do not track it): ___%
- Working days per year: 250

Daily orders x error rate x 250 = annual errors.

Example: 300 orders/day x 0.03 x 250 = 2,250 errors/year.

**Step 2: Assign your cost per error.**

Start with direct costs only. Investigation time (CSR hourly rate x 30 to 60 minutes), credit note processing, return shipping, re-ship cost. For most distributors this falls between $150 and $300 per error.

Then consider the blended cost. Add a conservative factor for relationship damage. Industry data puts the fully loaded figure at $18,000, but that includes worst-case churn scenarios. A reasonable middle ground for planning purposes: $400 to $600 per error for a distributor with average customer lifetime values.

**Step 3: Calculate annual cost.**

Annual errors x cost per error = annual error cost.

At 2,250 errors and $200 direct cost: **$450,000/year.**
At 2,250 errors and $500 blended cost: **$1,125,000/year.**

**Step 4: Factor in what is not in the formula.**

The calculation above covers identifiable errors. It does not capture customer churn you cannot attribute, the institutional knowledge risk when experienced staff leave, or the opportunity cost of your team spending 20 to 30% of their time on error correction instead of revenue-generating work.

Your actual cost is higher than the formula produces. The formula gives you the floor.

**Step 5: Model the reduction.**

If AI-based processing drops your error rate from 3% to under 1% (consistent with the Meesenburg production results), your annual error count drops from 2,250 to under 750. At $200 direct cost per error, that is $300,000 saved. At $500 blended cost, $750,000.

The question is not whether to address this. The question is how fast you can get there. If you want to see what AI-based processing does with your actual orders, not a demo dataset, [send us a few of your messiest ones](/contact). We will process them and show you the output. If it works, we talk further. If it does not, you have lost 20 minutes.
